rComments: Make sure to do the readings and pay attention in lecture - she doesn't do any surprises and really shapes you for the exam. TA marking was hard but overall such a great course! One of my fave geo profs at uoft.

The lecture notes are very well organized and she doesn't stray away from them or get carried away. If you're sick, it isn't an issue. Stay home and read the PowerPoint. She won't penalize you and she doesn't hide anything from students who can't make it to class.

This class is overall very fun and easy to relate to in terms of content. As long as you complete the weekly readings and attend lectures, you are promised a good mark. The outlines of assignments and exams were very clear and there were no surprises.

Professor Buckley is very caring and passionate about what she teaches. I looked forward to attending lecture every week because they were so amazing. She gives a very clear outline of the course. It is one reading and podcast every week which is beyond reasonable. You have to put the work in for an A. I would recommend this class to everyone.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Amazing lectures', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: The Prof is awesome and shares really great content. She really tries to make the learning experience accessible. However, the prof is bad with emails.

Prof Buckley is a very caring, wonderful professor. Her lectures are great and the exams/assignments are more than fair. The only issue I had was that she took very long to email back and in some instances didnt even answer
Great, caring, engaging prof who wants the best for her students

SHE IS AMAZINGGG! She is very kind and will listen to you when you ask for help/ clarification on why you may have lost marks. She explains concepts super well and overall she respects her students! 1 podcast and 1 reading every week, but she goes over key points in class.

Prof. Buckley is a very good lecturer, her slides are informative and she is a good orator. She stays on topic and is clear and concise. Something odd I noticed about her is that she is sometimes apologetic and worried she is "boring" our class. If you ever read this, know that you're not boring at all!

Easily one of the best professors in Geography. She's always clear about terms/concepts, tells you exactly what to look for in readings, and assignments and exams are extremely fair. Would definitely take her other courses!
Great motivating professor, time flew in the class and I really enjoyed the entire course!

All courses by Professor Buckley are well taught, clear and she brings in real-life examples.  She is always available at her office hours or after class.  She will guide you through essays and exams.  One of the best professors in Geography and she cares.  Not tough or demanding with readings etc.  Great marks too!
Would be useful to have timely response to email. problem is, it didn't come at all!
Never replied to the only e-mail valid question I asked. Not very helpful at all.

New prof that's great with explaining concepts in class. I would say you should read the readings she assigns to do well on the midterm and final. The assignments were marked fairly as well. Great prof and really nice as well.

prof. buckley is a new prof at utsc, with that being said I think she did a great job in lecturing. her slides are very informative, so its not really necessary to go to class. her exams are very fair. assignments are fair too. i like how she respond to emails pretty quickly and she is very helpful!
